Excellent — I have everything I need. Here are the **5 most important key points** from *GUIDE-039: Add Income Surveys Quick Guide*, each with a Jira citation status:

---

### 1. 🎯 Income Surveys are a Special Provision Program tool — not free/reduced benefit applications
Districts enrolled in a Special Provision Program use Income Surveys to collect and submit household income data for **state funding compliance**, bypassing the standard free/reduced meal application process. This is the fundamental reason the feature exists.

> **[VERIFIED: NXT-19154]** — *"Family Hub SC - Apply/Application Template - Add full support for Income Surveys"* confirms Income Surveys are a distinct path for eligible districts, with dedicated template handling separate from standard applications.

---

### 2. 🧭 A 7-step process wizard (with a purple active-step indicator) guides data entry
The entire workflow flows through a sequential wizard: **Students → Household → Details → Contact Info → Comments → Review → Summary**. The purple highlight on the wizard header always shows the user which step they are on, reducing entry errors.

> **[VERIFIED: NXT-19085]** — *"Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Students Step - Add/Find a Student"* explicitly verifies that the wizard page displays when "Add New Survey" is selected and that the wizard controls step-by-step progression.

---

### 3. 👤 The Students step supports both finding existing students and creating new ones (PENDING status), with automatic household sibling suggestions
Users can search by name or ID to add existing students. If siblings exist in the same household, the system **automatically suggests** adding them. Manually added new students receive a **PENDING** status and can be edited or deleted before proceeding.

> **[VERIFIED: NXT-19085]** — *"Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Students Step - Add/Find a Student"* directly covers both the find-a-student and add-a-student functions, as well as the PENDING status behavior.

---

### 4. 🏠 The Household step branches into two mutually exclusive response types: Special Assistance vs. Income
- **Special Assistance**: Select a Case Type and enter a Case Number (must match a required format).
- **Income**: Enter Household Size, select a Frequency, and select an Income Range from dropdowns.

This branching logic is the most data-critical decision in the form — choosing the wrong type would invalidate the entire survey.

> **[VERIFIED: NXT-19086]** — *"Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Household Step"* confirms the Household step exists within the wizard and that its acceptance criteria validate the step's full functionality.

---

### 5. ✅ At Review, users can either SUBMIT immediately or MARK AS PENDING to save for later; the Summary step provides a PDF export
After reviewing all sections, staff have a safety valve: **MARK AS PENDING** saves the survey without submitting, allowing a second review. Once submitted, a confirmation appears and the **Summary step offers a PDF export button**, plus an "Add Another Survey" option for batch entry.

> **[VERIFIED: NXT-19092]** — *"Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Review Step"* confirms the submit/pending decision point at review. Additionally **[VERIFIED: NXT-19094]** — *"Income Surveys - Add New Survey - Summary"* confirms the post-submission Summary step with PDF export and continuation options. See also **NXT-20510** (*"Income Survey - Edit Survey Details - Process/Make Pending/Delete/Restore Survey"*) which further confirms the Pending status lifecycle.

---

